The method should return an integer value representing the length of the maximum size turbulent subarray of `arr`.
The method should not modify the input array `arr`.
The method should handle both positive and negative integers in the array `arr`.
The method should handle cases where the maximum size turbulent subarray is at the beginning, middle, or end of the array `arr`.
The method should handle cases where there are multiple maximum size turbulent subarrays in the array `arr`.
The method should handle cases where there is no turbulent subarray in the array `arr`, in which case it should return 0.
